		<div id="comment_body_64304195"><p>One of my ocd bug a boos.</p><p>IQ was never intended as a general measure of intelligence.</p><p>It was specifically designed to provide a simple metric to compare one -young- child's intellectual and educational state vs others on a group scale.</p><p>It was absolutely not designed to provide a metric for adults since there's a "divide score by age in months" in the calculation.</p><p>Rant over.  Thank you.</p></div>
